-- Baseball Suspends Pitcher Mota 100 Games for Positive Drug Test
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2012-05-07T20:18:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-07/baseball-suspends-pitcher-mota-100-games-for-positive-drug-test.html
San Francisco Giants pitcher Guillermo
Mota has been suspended 100 games by  Major League Baseball  for
testing positive for a performance-enhancing substance.  Mota, 38, previously received a 50-game ban in November
2006.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  